# Kubernetes Pod Diagnostics System üõ†Ô∏èü§ñ

## Overview

The **Kubernetes Pod Diagnostics System** is an intelligent web-based tool that analyzes Kubernetes pods and provides clear, structured diagnostics along with AI-powered explanations. It combines Kubernetes API-driven analysis with a conversational Large Language Model (LLM) to make pod troubleshooting faster, simpler, and more intuitive.

This system helps users:

* Diagnose failing or unstable pods
* Understand root causes in plain language
* Interactively discuss issues with an AI assistant
* Receive actionable remediation steps

---

## Key Features

### ‚úÖ Real-time Pod Diagnostics

* Fetches live pod data using Kubernetes Python client
* Analyzes status, events, and logs
* Identifies common issues like:

  * CrashLoopBackOff
  * ImagePullBackOff
  * Pending / Scheduling failures
  * Network connectivity errors

### ü§ñ AI-Powered Explanations (Groq LLM)

* Integrated Groq Cloud LLM for conversational troubleshooting
* Users can ask follow-up questions such as:

  * "Why is this pod failing?"
  * "How can I fix this issue?"
  * "Is this problem critical?"
* AI responses are contextual, based on real diagnostic results

### üéØ Smart State Management

* Diagnosis runs only once per pod
* AI chat continues without re-triggering diagnostics
* Switching pods resets chat automatically for clean flow

### üåô Professional Dark UI

* Modern, minimal, Kubernetes-inspired layout
* Streamlit-based responsive interface
* Sidebar-driven cluster ‚Üí namespace ‚Üí pod selection

---

